main event: Two objects were observed moving in the eastern sky for approximately 2 hours and 45 minutes on February 23, 1964, in Manchester, New Hampshire.
interesting points: The sighting lasted longer than 2 hours, possibly indicating something of significance,The witness believed that the objects were not typical aircraft or celestial bodies such as Venus or Jupiter,The sighting generated multiple calls to the police from concerned citizens,At least one member of the New Hampshire State Police reported seeing the objects,The objects were potentially mistaken for large balloons or astronomical phenomena but were described as unusually large.
